---
description: Enforce Dart class/file and formatting commit rules
alwaysApply: true
---

- Keep one class per Dart file.
- Do not create multi-class Dart files.
- When touching a legacy multi-class Dart file, split classes into separate files.
- Before any commit, run `dart format .`.
- Include formatter-produced changes in the commit.
- Do not hardcode user-facing strings; add/use localization entries from `lib/l10n`.
- Use design tokens from `lib/core/theme/*` for color and typography (including font sizes).
- Avoid introducing new ad-hoc colors or font sizes unless required.
- If required, add new tokens under `lib/core/theme` first, then use those tokens.
